Description:
------------

This example is part of BAT. It will only run if BAT is correctly
installed on the system.

The example shows how to use the histogram fitter which comes with
BAT. It fits a const + Gaussian function to a histogram assuming
Poissonian uncertainties in each bin.

The source file(s) contain(s) plenty of comments and explanations.
For further information, see the manual at

https://bat.github.io/bat-docs/master/manual/html/


Files:
------

  README                    - this file
  histogramFitterExample.C  - the source code of the main program


Running the example:
--------------------

1. Make sure that BAT is correctly installed in the system.

2. Run the macro in a ROOT session, e.g., with 'root histogramFitterExample.C'
